title: For Sale:  DPMS .308 Bull 24" w/Upgrades (RFLR-308-A3-JP-VH)

Available at www.NelsonTactical.com

In 2001, DPMS expanded from its share of the .223/5.56mm market, and exploded onto the .308 rifle scene. The LR-308, the first and foremost of the .308 line, and for which the rifle series is named, is a rifle to be reckoned with. So much so that it was named the NRA Rifle of the year in 2005.
With a 24” stainless bull barrel, 1 in 10 twist and free floating handguard and a flat top receiver for easier mounting of optics, the LR-308 has gone toe to toe with bolt action rifles and delivered comparable accuracy, with higher magazine capacity and rate of fire. The conventional thought that "only a bolt action could be considered a precision rifle" has been in contention ever since.
This rifle features several factory installed modifications including replacing the slick side high rise upper receiver with an A3 upper receiver with forward assist, shell deflector and dust cover. title: For Sale/Trade:  Egyptian Hakim 8mm Battle Rifle
postcontent:
I have an Hakim 8mm semi-auto battle rifle I might be interested in trading for the right offer. Looking for unique firearms that I couldn't go out and find locally.

Internals/metal are in good shape. Bolt functions like it should, and there has been no cutting or bubba type shenanigans anywhere. This gun is stock.
The wood has some dings in it, but they're minor and could be cleaned up if someone was so inclined. I didn't want to alter this rifle in any way, so I haven't tried.

These were made in the 50's and 60's by Egypt using machines that originally made the Swedish AG-42, which is similar in action but a different caliber.
These rifles were some of the first direct impingement battle rifles. Only 70,000 or so were ever made, and of that only a couple thousand were imported into the US. They have an adjustable gas system, excellent muzzle break, and are fed by 10 round detachable box magazines.

The bore is PRISTINE and it shoots straight as an arrow. Took it out recently and put about 60 rounds of Yugo FMJ through it and it ran flawlessly.
Have a couple boxes of ammo still on clips to go with it.

Any other questions, just ask.

title: For Sale:  Custom 3 Keg Kegerator
postcontent:
I know this isn't really arms related for the most part, but I like guns, and I like beer, so maybe there is someone out there like me, who might need this! This is a custom made 3 keg capacity kegerator. It has the ability to run a 16 gal main keg, and two pony kegs. Currently it is setup/plumbed for 2 kegs, one 16 gal, and one pony keg. You would have the ability to modify it to run 3 kegs easily, as I originally intended to to do just that, but I ended up with only two at this point. The kegerator is made out of a full size fridge, which has lots of storage room on the upper shelf for glasses and cans/bottle of your non-kegged beer. There is also shelf space in the door for glasses/cans. The fridge does have a small freezer in the bottom, I would say about 1 cubic foot or so. I chose this fridge specifically for the small lower freezer, so there would be ample space for multiple kegs, but you could still freese glasses if you wanted to. The fridge gets cold fast and stays that way. This setup comes with a 20 pound co2 tank that has a dual gauge regulator (tank pressure/output pressure) as well as internal valving in the fridge, so you can shut off each keg individually, and the tank currently has about 850 pounds of pressure in it. You will probably be able to runs kegs off that amount of co2 for years! There is a custom made stainless steel drip tray attached to the front with internal resovior, so you don't have to set a bucket under the taps for someone to kick over all the time. Resovior is mounted inside the fridge door. All the fittings, taps, pour spouts, co2 and beer lines were all ordered from professional beer outlets. I will also throw in a 16 gal empty keg to use as your first deposit, saving you at least $50 on your first keg purchase! I also have some spare parts that will go with the setup also. All speed stickers come free of charge! I am selling this kegerator only because it has been a while since I have used it, and it is taking up space in my garage. I am confident you will get lots of use out of it. I have it cold now, and if you get it to your place and setup quickly, you could be drinking ice cold kegged beer within minutes!

I am looking for $400 for this kegerator setup. That being said I would be interested in possible partial trade for certain firearms or reloading equipment.. I am looking for a Ruger 10/22, Glock 23, bolt action .22lr rifle, , bolt action .223, and few others. Email or call me for more info, or to let me know what you might be willing to trade. You haul, I will not deliver. Glassware in pics not inlcuded. If you have any questions, please call Aeron at 406-five four four-8258, or shoot me an email. I get all email right to my phone, so I should be able to reply quickly. Thanks for looking.
